    <descript>
      <abstract>This file contains the boundaries of the Board of Supervisors election districts derived from 2000 US census.  The layer also contains the voting precincts inside each district, which is location of polling places for each district.</abstract>
      <purpose>This data was produced in compliance with the constitution of the Commonwealth of Virginia, which mandates counties to redraw their Board of Supervisor election districts based of the results of the most recent decennial census, in this case 2000.</purpose>
      <supplinf>Data are stored in the corporate ArcSDE Geodatabase as a polygon feature class.  The coordinate system is Virginia State Plane (North), Zone 4501, datum NAD83 HARN (vertical datum, if applicable, NAVD88), US Survey foot units.</supplinf>
    </descript>

      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Original Census Bureau Tiger/Line files were transformed into an ArcInfo coverage .  The federally defined census blocks were grouped into proposed Supervisor Districts.  Upon approval by BoS, the districts were then divided into Precincts to facilitate the allocation of polling places.  Some minor edits have occured since initial compilation.</procdesc>

        <proccont>

      <procstep>
        <procdesc>At the Board's direction, Paeonian Springs was relocated from Clarks Gap to Waterford precinct.</procdesc>
        <procdate>2003</procdate>
        <proccont>
          <cntinfo>

      <procstep>
        <procdesc>This data set was part of a batch process that converted legacy data from ArcInfo coverage in Librarian to a single-tiled ArcInfo coverage in preparation for a final conversion to ArcSDE Geodatabase Feature Classes.  Data were extracted from Librarian using the EXTRACT TOPOLOGICAL command.
Multi-tiled data sets were extracted into multiple coverages and then combined based on the feature type(s).  Layers with both polygon and arc feature classes were processed with the Arc commands, MAPJOIN and DISSOLVE.  Arc feature classes alone were processed with the Arc commands, APPEND and DISSOLVE.  Layers with both arc and point feature classes and point feature classes alone were processed with the Arc command, APPEND.  When used, the arc command, DISSOLVE, was given with the <#all> option.
All coverages were then reprojected to HARN83 using the following .prj file specifications:
INPUT
PROJECTION STATEPLANE
UNITS FEET
ZONE 5551
DATUM NAD27 NADCON
PARAMETERS
OUTPUT
PROJECTION STATEPLANE
UNITS FEET
FIPSZONE 4501
DATUM HPGN NADCON
PARAMETERS END

The dataset was then converted to a feature class in a geodatabase in ArcSDE.</procdesc>
        <procdate>2004</procdate>
        <proccont>

        </proccont>
      </procstep>
      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Eight precincts split into new precincts either individually or jointly with another existing precinct.  The individual split involved taking a single existng precinct and splitting it into two new precincts.  The other type of split involved adjoining precincts.  Part of each precinct would be split from the original and combined to make the new precinct.

New Precincts created: Newton-Lee (814), Belmont Ridge (815), Briar Woods (111), Freedom (112), and Tolbert (410)</procdesc>
        <procdate>November 2006</procdate>
        <proccont>
          <cntinfo>
            <cntorgp>

            <cntpos>GIS Systems Analyst</cntpos>

            <cntvoice/>
          </cntinfo>
        </proccont>
      </procstep>
      <procstep>
        <procdesc>Five existing precincts were split into ten new precincts upon approval by the Loudoun County Board of Supervisors in July 2007.  New precinct boundary lines were designated along street centerlines & stream networks.  Two of the precincts were also renamed during this process.  Lovettsville was renamed to West Lovettsville & Riverbend to River Bend.

New Precincts created: Countryside (213), East Lovettsville (411), Heritage (412), Brandon Park (506), & South Bank (609)

Existing Precincts split: River Bend (207), Lovettsville (401), Greenway (405), Cool Spring (505), and Lowes Island (607).</procdesc>
        <procdate>September 2007</procdate>
